{
  "name": "Iridescent Salamander",
  "type": "ancestry",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>Your companion is an iridescent salamander, an unusually large amphibian that uses its reflective color-changing skin to confuse its enemies.</p><p><strong>Size</strong> Small</p><p><strong>Melee</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">1</span> jaws (finesse), Damage 1d6 piercing</p><p><strong>Str</strong> +2, <strong>Dex</strong> +3, <strong>Con</strong> +2, <strong>Int</strong> –4, <strong>Wis</strong> +1, <strong>Cha</strong> +0</p><p><strong>Hit Points</strong> 6</p><p><strong>Skill</strong> Survival</p><p><strong>Senses</strong> darkvision</p><p><strong>Speed</strong> 20 feet, climb 20 feet, swim 20 feet</p><p><strong>Support Benefit</strong> Your salamander reflects the light on its scales that shine brightly. Until the start of your next turn, if you hit and deal damage to a creature adjacent to your salamander, the creature is @UUID[Compendium.sf2e.conditions.Item.TkIyaNPgTZFBCCuh]{Dazzled} until the start of your next turn unless its level is higher than yours.</p><p><strong>Advanced Maneuver</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-animal-companions.sf-AC-Advanced-Maneuvers.Item.hsX60mynCaIndLpp]{Color Swirl}</p>"
    },
